### Reflection in C#

Reflection provides the ability to inspect types, methods, properties, and fields at runtime, and to invoke members dynamically.

### Getting Type Information

```csharp
using System.Reflection;

// Get Type object
Type type1 = typeof(string);
Type type2 = "hello".GetType();
Type? type3 = Type.GetType("System.String");

Console.WriteLine($"Name: {type1.Name}");
Console.WriteLine($"FullName: {type1.FullName}");
Console.WriteLine($"Namespace: {type1.Namespace}");
Console.WriteLine($"IsClass: {type1.IsClass}");
Console.WriteLine($"IsValueType: {type1.IsValueType}");
Console.WriteLine($"BaseType: {type1.BaseType}");
```

### Inspecting Members

```csharp
Type type = typeof(List<int>);

// Methods
foreach (MethodInfo method in type.GetMethods(BindingFlags.Public | BindingFlags.Instance))
    Console.WriteLine($"Method: {method.Name}");

// Properties
foreach (PropertyInfo prop in type.GetProperties())
    Console.WriteLine($"Property: {prop.Name}, Type: {prop.PropertyType.Name}");

// Fields
foreach (FieldInfo field in type.GetFields())
    Console.WriteLine($"Field: {field.Name}");
```

### Dynamic Invocation

```csharp
Type type = typeof(Math);
MethodInfo? method = type.GetMethod("Max", new[] { typeof(int), typeof(int) });

if (method != null)
{
    object? result = method.Invoke(null, new object[] { 10, 20 });
    Console.WriteLine(result);  // 20
}
```

### Creating Instances

```csharp
// Using Activator
Type type = typeof(StringBuilder);
object? instance = Activator.CreateInstance(type);

// With constructor arguments
instance = Activator.CreateInstance(type, new object[] { "Hello" });
```

### Reflection at Assembly Level

```csharp
Assembly assembly = Assembly.GetExecutingAssembly();
Console.WriteLine($"Assembly: {assembly.FullName}");

Assembly loadAssembly = Assembly.Load("System.Text.Json");

foreach (Type t in assembly.GetTypes())
    Console.WriteLine(t.Name);
```

### Performance Considerations

| Aspect | Impact |
|--------|--------|
| Type checking | Minor (typeof, is, as) |
| Member enumeration | Moderate |
| Dynamic invocation | Slow (10-100x slower) |
| Expression trees | Faster alternative |
| Source generators | Best performance (compile-time) |

### Use Cases

```csharp
// Dependency injection containers
// Serialization/deserialization
// Plugin systems
// Unit testing frameworks
// Code analysis tools
// Attribute-based validation
```

> **Key Point:** Reflection is powerful but slow. Use it for scenarios that require runtime type discovery. For performance-critical code, prefer expression trees or source generators. Reflection can break with code obfuscation or trimming.

### Accessing Private Members

```csharp
Type type = typeof(MyClass);
FieldInfo? field = type.GetField("_secret", BindingFlags.NonPublic | BindingFlags.Instance);
object? value = field?.GetValue(instance);
```

### Getting Custom Attributes

```csharp
Type type = typeof(MyClass);
var attrs = type.GetCustomAttributes(typeof(SerializableAttribute), false);
```

### Reflection with Generics

